---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Assaf Barnir — Unscared OS"
  description="Who is Assaf — the person behind the OS."
  ogTitle="About Assaf Barnir"
  ogDescription="Builder, author, CS leader. The person behind the Unscared OS."
  ogImage="/og/about.png"
>
  <section class="hero" style="min-height: 60vh; text-align: left; align-items: flex-start; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding-top: 140px;">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="hero-headline" style="font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 52px);">
      The person behind<br />the OS.
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div style="max-width: 680px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-muted);">
      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; color: var(--text);">
        I'm an engineer who's spent my career in the gap between technical teams and the humans they serve.
        CS, Solutions Engineering, Support, TAM — I've built them from scratch, scaled them,
        and learned what actually works (and what doesn't).
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
        Three verticals isn't a portfolio strategy. It's the honest map of what I'm actually doing:
        building software that helps people (Scale Yourself), tools that compound with AI
        (Scale Intelligence), and frameworks for leading teams through the transition
        (Scale Business).
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
        The Unscared OS thesis isn't abstract. It's the pattern I kept seeing:
        the people who thrive in the AI era aren't the ones with the best models —
        they're the ones whose human operating system is solid enough to leverage them.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
        Four books, thirteen products, hundreds of hires. I know what the table
        looks like from every side. Now building for the AI era without fear.
      </p>

      <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content: flex-start;">
        <a href="/work-with-me" class="btn-primary">Work with me</a>
        <a href="/library" class="btn-ghost">Read the books</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
